sentences: Adam Michael Neely (born 1988) is an American YouTuber, bassist and composer.

Neely graduated from Berklee College of Music with a B. A in Jazz Composition in 2009 and in 2012, received a Masters of Music in Jazz Composition from The Manhattan School of Music as directed under Jim McNeely.

Neely graduated from Berklee College of Music with a B. A in Jazz Composition in 2009 and in 2012, received a Masters of Music in Jazz Composition from The Manhattan School of Music as directed under Jim McNeely.
He was awarded the Herb Alpert ASCAP Young Jazz Composer award in 2012 and 2015 as well as the Jerome Fund commission prize in 2014, for his work "Exigence".
He was awarded the Herb Alpert ASCAP Young Jazz Composer award in 2012 and 2015 as well as the Jerome Fund commission prize in 2014, for his work "Exigence".
On May 18-20, 2019, Adam Neely, as a member of the band Aberdeen, was hired by the United States Department of State to go to Kyrgyzstan on a three-day tour that included two concerts and a workshop.
In December 2019, Neely earned a spot in the New Yorker's annual Christmas Poem.

In 2020, Neely defended Katy Perry's use of an ostinato in the song "Dark Horse" after she was sued by the rapper Flame.
Starting May of 2020, Adam Neely started posting his videos ad-free on Nebula Streaming Service as part of the Standard Creator Community, with some exclusive and extended cut videos on the service.
